Common.Highlight.Common.Text: New 10 year lease to Corfield IGA

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE Western Australian Retail Investments as exclusive selling agents are excited to present the Corfield Shopping Centre For Sale by an International Expressions of Interest campaign.

This offering presents the unique opportunity to acquire an IGA anchored shopping centre on a significant site in one of the fastest growing areas in Australia. 

The centre is situated opposite the Seaforth Primary School and under 1,500 metres to the Seaforth Train Station on the arterial Corfield Street. Corfield Shopping Centre is located within the southeast growth corridor of Perth in the suburb of Gosnells with a strong 4.50% pa strong future population growth expected in the primary trade area. 

Key features are;
- Strategically located IGA anchored shopping centre adjacent the Seaforth Primary School and approximately 1,200 metres from the Seaforth Train Station. 
- Over 94% leased with a strong 4.8 year WALE (by income) and a fully leased income of approximately $760,000. 
- Newly executed 10 year leases to Corfield IGA anchor tenant and mini-major Corfield Tavern providing for over 55% of the gross income and over 60% of the NLA for the centre. 
- Quality mix of local and national specialty tenant mix with favourable 3% - 5% rental escalations.
- Large 1.12Ha corner site with ample at grade parking and additional future development upside.

Corfield Shopping Centre is being offered for sale by an International Expressions of Interest campaign closing the 7th of April 2021 at 3pm AWST.

Leased retail investment property with an attractive rental income stream in a prominent main street location.

Anchored by Super Cheap Auto Pty Ltd, a division of the Super Retail Group Ltd being one of Australasia's Top 10 corporate retailers and which is listed in the Australia Stock Exchange.

Gross income approximately $198,500pa.

Net income approximately $176,000pa.
